docker containers 
    - contain app dependancies, 
    - os level dependancies, 
    - etc etc
    - eliminates environment mismatches


What is it:
    - not virtualization
    - class of its own


VMS:
    - portaable, lots of overhead
    - predictable
    - slow

CM Tools:
    - less portable, minimal overhead
    - not reproducible
    - needs config management tools

Docker:
    - in between


Workflows
    - dev
    - build
    - deploy


Docker registry
    - deploy framework



